org.corfudb.runtime.view.stream

Class BackpointerStreamView

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.corfudb.runtime.view.stream.AbstractContextStreamView<org.corfudb.runtime.view.stream.AbstractQueuedStreamView.QueuedStreamContext>
      • org.corfudb.runtime.view.stream.AbstractQueuedStreamView
        • org.corfudb.runtime.view.stream.BackpointerStreamView
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Iterator<ILogData>, IStreamView

    public class BackpointerStreamView
extends AbstractQueuedStreamView
    A view of a stream implemented with backpointers.

    In this implementation, all addresses are global (log) addresses.

    All method calls of this class are thread-safe.

    Created by mwei on 12/11/15.

        Description copied from class: AbstractQueuedStreamView
        Defines the strategy to discover addresses belonging to this stream. We currently support two mechanisms: - Following backpointers (@see org.corfudb.runtime.view.stream.BackpointerStreamView) - Requesting the sequencer for the complete address map of a stream. (@see org.corfudb.runtime.view.stream.AddressMapStreamView)
        Specified by:
        discoverAddressSpace in class AbstractQueuedStreamView
        Parameters:
        streamId - stream unique identifier.
        queue - queue to fill up.
        startAddress - read start address (inclusive)
        stopAddress - read stop address (exclusive)
        filter - filter to apply to data
        checkpoint - true if checkpoint discovery, false otherwise.
        maxGlobal - max address to resolve discovery.
        Returns:
        true if addresses were discovered, false, otherwise.
